  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable peace, security and integration for poor and vulnerable urban communities in Kenya by 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries:
 About 300 (180 males and 120 females) members of various sports teams  at SSS  and other 2764 members of the community who will be directly through proposed project activities (1640 males and  1104 females). 
Indirect beneficiaries
The project estimates that it will be able to reach about 25,000 (15,000 males and10,000 females) through the outlined open  project activities such as sports , radio programmes and peace walks. 

This project aims to promote sustainable peace, security and integration for poor and vulnerable urban communities in Kenya by 2021
SSS will seek to enhance citizen participation in devolved government through civic education based on human rights approach. SSS will build mutual partnerships with the Sub-County and Ward Administrators and other like-minded entities in order to improve service delivery, Organize a series of accountability forums where duty bearers will come to report progress of their legal duties to the residents of Korogocho. 

 These forums will be facilitated by a team of community peer educators who will be direct beneficiaries partly of SSS accountability trainings. They will be organized through a revamped community participation framework called Community Education and Leadership Teams (CELTs). Each of the nine villages of Korogocho will have a CELT committee whose responsibility will be to mobilize community members in their villages to participate in various governance agenda as well as conducting Focused Group Discussions (FGDs) in their respective villages. This will be aimed at campaigning for the establishment of Village Councils as outlined in sections 52 and 53 of the County Government Act 2012 that has been kept in abeyance for the last 4 years.</narrative>
  </description>
